file='18_input_datasets_buf_1993-2020_180x360_update.nc'

    ds3 = ds2.sel(name=names_local)
    
    glb_ts_mm=np.zeros((len(names_local),len(ds2.tdec)))
    glb_ts_mm[:,:]='nan'
    #% % loop over datasets and time
    for iname,n in enumerate(names_local):
        print(n)
        value=np.array(ds3.SL_mm[iname,:,:,:])
        
        mask_data=np.array(value[180,:,:])
        mask_data[np.where(mask_data==0)]='nan'
        mask_data[np.isfinite(mask_data)]=1
        # plt.pcolor(mask_data);plt.show()

        mu=(da.data*grid_area*mask_data).sum(dim=('lat','lon'))/ocean_area
        # mu=mu.where(mu!=0,'nan')
        glb_ts_mm[iname,:]=np.array(mu.data)

    for idx,name in enumerate(names_local):

        # if np.any(np.isnan(data)):

        if idx ==0 or idx ==1:
            data[0:114]='nan'
            # data[112]='nan'
        df_glb[name]=data-mu

    df_glb_local = df_glb[names_local]
    df_glb_local['time'] = df_glb['time']

    tr[ireg]=out[0]

def OLS_model(time,height,ci=99):
    # Remove any nans:
    acc_idx = np.isfinite(height)
    
    #Build Design Matrix:
    design_matrix=np.ones([np.sum(acc_idx),6])
    design_matrix[:,1]=time[acc_idx]-np.nanmean(time) #time
    design_matrix[:,2]=np.cos(2*np.pi*time[acc_idx]) # cos-annual
    design_matrix[:,3]=np.sin(2*np.pi*time[acc_idx]) # sin-annual
    design_matrix[:,4]=np.cos(2*np.pi*2*time[acc_idx]) #cos-semi-annual
    design_matrix[:,5]=np.sin(2*np.pi*2*time[acc_idx]) #sin semi-annual
    
    #Fit OLS to the matrix
    solution=np.linalg.lstsq(design_matrix,height[acc_idx],rcond=None)[0]
    trend=solution[1] # trend
    pred=np.matmul(design_matrix[:,(0,1)],solution[0:2]) # predicted sign
    OLSmodel=np.matmul(design_matrix,solution)

    # compute interval confidence
    ci_z = {
    80:1.282,
    85:1.440,
    90:1.645,
    95:1.960,
    99:2.576,
    99.5:2.807,
    99.9:3.291
    }
    # build covariance matrix:
    ssxm, ssxym, _, ssym = np.cov(time[acc_idx],height[acc_idx], bias=1).flat
    # # R-value
    r = ssxym / np.sqrt(ssxm * ssym)
    df = len(height) - 2  # Number of degrees of freedom
    slope_stderr = np.sqrt((1 - r**2) * ssym / ssxm / df)

    error= ci_z[ci]*slope_stderr # 99% confidence interval
    return trend,error,pred, OLSmodel

def trend_fun(time,height,ci=99,window=10,min_len=5,freq=1):
    # window and min_len in years
    # frequency is the amount of measurements in one year (i.e., monthly data = 12)
    time_acc_idx = np.isfinite(height)
    height = height[time_acc_idx]
    time = time[time_acc_idx]
    
    # normal trend
    trend, error, pred, OLSmodel = OLS_model(time,height,ci=ci)
    
    # Roling trend
    trend_rol = np.full_like(height,np.nan)
    error_rol = np.full_like(height,np.nan)
    half_window = np.int((window*freq)/ 2)
    for idx, yr in enumerate(time):
        idx_start = np.max([0, idx - half_window])
        idx_stop = np.min([len(time), idx + half_window])
        years = time[idx_start:idx_stop]
        if len(years) >=(window*freq):
            out = OLS_model(years,height[idx_start:idx_stop],ci=ci)
            trend_rol[idx]=out[0]
            error_rol[idx]=out[1]


    # moving_trend
    idx_end=-1
    trend_mov = np.full_like(time,np.nan)
    error_mov = np.full_like(time,np.nan)
    
    for idx, first_year in enumerate(time[::-1][:]):
        idx_start = - np.max([idx,(min_len*freq)])
        years = time[idx_start:idx_end]
        if len(years) >= (min_len*freq) and len(years)>2:
            # print(years)
            out = OLS_model(years,height[idx_start:idx_end],ci=ci)
            trend_mov[-idx]=out[0]
            error_mov[-idx]=out[1]
        
    
    time_dim = hv.Dimension('time',label='Time',unit='years')
    height_dim = hv.Dimension('height',label='Height',unit='mm')
    trend_dim1 = hv.Dimension('moving trend',label='Trend',unit='mm/year')
    trend_dim = hv.Dimension('trend',label='Trend',unit='mm/year')
    
    ## standard
    curve_trend = hv.Curve((time,pred),
                           time_dim,height_dim,
                           label='trend').opts(color='red')
    curve_OLS = hv.Curve((time,OLSmodel),
                           time_dim,height_dim,
                           label='OLS model').opts(color='blue',line_width=0.5)
    
    er_up_trend = hv.Curve((time,pred+error),
                           time_dim,height_dim,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')
    er_lo_trend = hv.Curve((time,pred-error),
                           time_dim,height_dim,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')
    scatter_height =  hv.Scatter((time,height),
                           time_dim,height_dim,
                           label='SLA').opts(color='blue')
        
    
    combine_height = hv.Overlay([scatter_height,curve_trend,er_lo_trend,er_up_trend,curve_OLS],label='SLA').opts(
        legend_position='top_left')
    
    
    ## rolling
    curve_trend_rol = hv.Curve((time,trend_rol),
                               time_dim,trend_dim,label='rolling trend').opts(color='green')
    
    er_up_trend_rol = hv.Curve((time,trend_rol+error_rol),
                           time_dim,trend_dim,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')
    
    er_lo_trend_rol = hv.Curve((time,trend_rol-error_rol),
                           time_dim,trend_dim,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')  
        
    cmin=np.nanmin(trend_rol - (2*error_rol) )
    cmax=np.nanmax(trend_rol + (2*error_rol) )
    
    cmin1=-2
    cmax1=6
    combine_rol = hv.Overlay([curve_trend_rol,er_lo_trend_rol,er_up_trend_rol],
                             label='{}-years Rolling Trend'.format(window)).opts(
        show_grid=True,
        ylim=(cmin,cmax),
        show_legend=False,
        legend_position='top_left')
    
    
  
    ## moving
    curve_trend_mov = hv.Curve((time,trend_mov),
                               time_dim,trend_dim1,
                               label='increasing trend').opts(color='blue')
    er_up_trend_mov = hv.Curve((time,trend_mov+error_mov),
                           time_dim,trend_dim1,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')
    
    er_lo_trend_mov = hv.Curve((time,trend_mov-error_mov),
                           time_dim,trend_dim1,
                           label='{}% CI'.format(ci)).opts(color='grey',alpha=0.5,line_dash='dashed')  
    
    cmin1=np.nanmin(trend_mov - 2*error_mov )
    cmax1=np.nanmax(trend_mov + 2*error_mov )
    
    cmin1=-2
    cmax1=6
    combine_mov = hv.Overlay([curve_trend_mov,er_lo_trend_mov,er_up_trend_mov],
                             label='Increasing Length Trend (min length:{})'.format(min_len)).opts(
        show_grid=True,
        ylim=(cmin1,cmax1),
        show_legend=False,
        legend_position='bottom_left')
      
    
    combine_curves = hv.Layout([combine_height, combine_rol, combine_mov]).cols(1)
    
    
#    return trend,error,pred,trend_rol,error_rol,trend_mov, error_mov
    return combine_curves.opts(width=700)# ,cmin1
